  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Water and Livelihood Development for Somaliland and Puntland</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH) activities in each project location. Construction of 2 boreholes, 2 shallow wells, 4 birkads, and 100 household latrines.

2) Livelihood interventions involving mainly livestock healthcare and restocking livestock to restore pastoralists&apos; livelihood base. 10,000 households will get livestock vaccinated and/or treated for lethal diseases. 1,000 households will receive seeds for better crop production. 2,000 households/IDPs affected by drought will receive life-saving food assistance.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To assist 78,000 poor pastoralists and agro-pastoralists affected by recurrent drought through livelihood and water development interventions.</narrative>
  </description>
